covered: Valid Deletion: Tests cover successful closure of an account via DELETE and verify the account is marked as closed (204).
Non-Existent Resource: Idempotent behavior is verified for non-existent accounts (204, no changes).

Query Parameters: Extensive coverage of boolean optional parameters, including default behavior, all-true, all-false, individual parameters, and all two-parameter combinations, plus ignoring extra parameters.
Authorization/Authentication: Tests cover missing required header (400) and missing/invalid authentication (401).
Input Validation and Security: Validation of invalid accountId formats (400), SQL injection attempts (400), and header-based XSS protection scenarios (204 with sanitized input).
Error Handling and Resilience: System error scenario (500) and transient failures with retry leading to idempotent success (TC14 and TC17).
Performance and Regression: Handling of large data with many subscriptions/invoices (TC07), and regression scenarios including unpaid invoices (TC19) and backward compatibility (TC20).
Edge Case: Unsupported/extra query parameters are ignored (TC13).
gaps: Concurrency: No explicit test for two simultaneous DELETE requests on the same account to exercise race conditions.
Rate Limiting: No tests asserting 429 responses or throttling behavior.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating ETag/Cache-Control headers or caching semantics for delete responses.
Authorization Nuance: No test for 403 Forbidden when authenticated but lacking permissions.
Invalid Parameter Values: No tests for invalid boolean parameter values (e.g., non-boolean strings) for query parameters.
recommendations: Add a concurrency test where two DELETE requests for the same account are issued in parallel to verify idempotence and correctness under race conditions.
Add rate-limiting tests to ensure proper 429 handling under bursts of DELETE requests.
Add caching-related tests to validate ETag/Cache-Control headers for DELETE responses if applicable.
Add a 403 Forbidden scenario to cover authorized users without sufficient permissions.
Add tests for invalid boolean param values to ensure input validation handles malformed query parameters gracefully.
